CSS positioning controls how elements are positioned in the document flow.

**1. Static Positioning (Default):**

```css
.static {
  position: static; /* Default value */
  /* top, right, bottom, left have no effect */
}
```

**2. Relative Positioning:**

```css
.relative {
  position: relative;
  top: 20px;    /* Moves 20px down from original position */
  left: 30px;   /* Moves 30px right from original position */
  /* Original space is preserved in document flow */
}
```

**3. Absolute Positioning:**

```css
.absolute {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50px;    /* 50px from top of nearest positioned ancestor */
  right: 20px;  /* 20px from right of nearest positioned ancestor */
  /* Removed from normal document flow */
}

/* Parent container must be positioned for absolute positioning */
.container {
  position: relative; /* Creates positioning context */
}
```

**4. Fixed Positioning:**

```css
.fixed {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  right: 0;
  /* Fixed relative to viewport, stays in place when scrolling */
}

/* Common use: Fixed navigation bar */
.navbar {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  z-index: 1000;
}
```

**5. Sticky Positioning:**

```css
.sticky {
  position: sticky;
  top: 20px; /* Becomes fixed when 20px from top of viewport */
  /* Behaves like relative until scroll threshold is met */
}

/* Common use: Sticky headers */
.sticky-header {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  background: white;
  z-index: 100;
}
```

**Complete Example:**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
.container {
  position: relative;
  width: 400px;
  height: 300px;
  border: 2px solid #333;
  margin: 50px;
}

.static-box {
  position: static;
  background: lightblue;
  padding: 10px;
  margin: 10px;
}

.relative-box {
  position: relative;
  top: 20px;
  left: 30px;
  background: lightgreen;
  padding: 10px;
}

.absolute-box {
  position: absolute;
  top: 10px;
  right: 10px;
  background: lightcoral;
  padding: 10px;
  width: 100px;
}

.fixed-nav {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  background: darkblue;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px;
  z-index: 1000;
}

.sticky-sidebar {
  position: sticky;
  top: 80px; /* Stick when 80px from top */
  float: right;
  width: 200px;
  background: lightyellow;
  padding: 10px;
  margin: 20px;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="fixed-nav">Fixed Navigation Bar</nav>

  <div style="margin-top: 80px;"> <!-- Account for fixed nav -->
    <div class="container">
      <div class="static-box">Static Box (normal flow)</div>
      <div class="relative-box">Relative Box (offset from original)</div>
      <div class="absolute-box">Absolute Box (positioned to container)</div>
    </div>

    <div class="sticky-sidebar">Sticky Sidebar</div>

    <!-- Add content to demonstrate scrolling -->
    <div style="height: 1500px; padding: 20px;">
      <p>Scroll to see sticky behavior...</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
```

**Key Differences:**

| Position | Document Flow | Positioned Relative To | Use Cases |
|----------|---------------|------------------------|----------|
| **static** | Normal flow | N/A | Default behavior |
| **relative** | Maintains space | Original position | Small adjustments |
| **absolute** | Removed from flow | Nearest positioned ancestor | Overlays, tooltips |
| **fixed** | Removed from flow | Viewport | Navigation bars, modals |
| **sticky** | Normal until threshold | Scroll container | Section headers |

**Z-index and Stacking Context:**

```css
/* Control stacking order for positioned elements */
.modal {
  position: fixed;
  z-index: 9999; /* Highest priority */
}

.dropdown {
  position: absolute;
  z-index: 100;
}

.tooltip {
  position: absolute;
  z-index: 50;
}
```

CSS Flexbox (Flexible Box Layout) is a layout method for arranging items in a one-dimensional space (row or column) with flexible sizing.

**1. Flex Container Properties:**

```css
.flex-container {
  display: flex; /* or inline-flex */

  /* Direction and wrapping */
  flex-direction: row; /* row | row-reverse | column | column-reverse */
  flex-wrap: nowrap;   /* nowrap | wrap | wrap-reverse */
  flex-flow: row nowrap; /* Shorthand for direction + wrap */

  /* Alignment */
  justify-content: flex-start; /* Main axis alignment */
  align-items: stretch;        /* Cross axis alignment */
  align-content: stretch;      /* Multi-line alignment */

  /* Spacing */
  gap: 10px; /* Space between items */
}
```

**2. Flex Item Properties:**

```css
.flex-item {
  /* Growth and shrinking */
  flex-grow: 0;     /* How much item should grow */
  flex-shrink: 1;   /* How much item should shrink */
  flex-basis: auto; /* Initial size before free space distribution */
  flex: 0 1 auto;   /* Shorthand: grow shrink basis */

  /* Individual alignment */
  align-self: auto; /* Override container's align-items */

  /* Ordering */
  order: 0; /* Change visual order without changing HTML */
}
```

