CSS Grid is a two-dimensional layout system that allows you to create complex layouts with rows and columns.

**1. Grid vs Flexbox:**

| Aspect | Grid | Flexbox |
|--------|------|----------|
| **Dimensions** | 2D (rows + columns) | 1D (row or column) |
| **Use Case** | Complex layouts | Component alignment |
| **Control** | Precise positioning | Flexible distribution |
| **Best For** | Page layouts | Navigation, cards |

**2. Basic Grid Setup:**

```css
.grid-container {
  display: grid;

  /* Define columns */
  grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 100px; /* Fixed, flexible, fixed */
  /* OR */
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); /* 3 equal columns */
  /* OR */
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); /* Responsive */

  /* Define rows */
  grid-template-rows: 80px auto 60px; /* Header, content, footer */

  /* Gaps */
  gap: 20px; /* Same as: row-gap: 20px; column-gap: 20px; */
}
```

**3. Grid Areas and Templates:**

```css
.layout-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas:
    "header header header"
    "sidebar main aside"
    "footer footer footer";
  grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 150px;
  grid-template-rows: 80px 1fr 60px;
  min-height: 100vh;
  gap: 10px;
}

/* Assign items to areas */
.header { grid-area: header; }
.sidebar { grid-area: sidebar; }
.main { grid-area: main; }
.aside { grid-area: aside; }
.footer { grid-area: footer; }
```

**4. Grid Item Positioning:**

```css
.grid-item {
  /* Position by line numbers */
  grid-column-start: 1;
  grid-column-end: 3;
  grid-row-start: 2;
  grid-row-end: 4;

  /* Shorthand */
  grid-column: 1 / 3; /* Start line 1, end line 3 */
  grid-row: 2 / 4;

  /* Even shorter */
  grid-area: 2 / 1 / 4 / 3; /* row-start / col-start / row-end / col-end */

  /* Span notation */
  grid-column: span 2; /* Span 2 columns */
  grid-row: span 3; /* Span 3 rows */
}
```

