**6. Advanced Grid Features:**

```css
/* Implicit grid (auto-generated rows/columns) */
.auto-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  grid-auto-rows: 100px; /* Height for auto-generated rows */
  grid-auto-flow: dense; /* Fill gaps automatically */
}

/* Fractional units and functions */
.advanced-grid {
  grid-template-columns:
    minmax(200px, 300px) /* Min 200px, max 300px */
    fit-content(400px)   /* Size to content, max 400px */
    1fr                  /* Remaining space */
    max-content;         /* Size to largest content */
}

/* Subgrid (limited browser support) */
.parent-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
}

.child-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-column: span 2;
  grid-template-columns: subgrid; /* Inherit parent's grid */
}
```

**7. When to Use Grid vs Flexbox:**

```css
/* Use Grid for: */
.page-layout { /* Overall page structure */
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas: "header header" "nav main" "footer footer";
}

/* Use Flexbox for: */
.navigation { /* Component alignment */
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}

.card-content { /* Content within cards */
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 10px;
}
```

