**CSS Specificity Order:**

```html
<style>
  p { color: blue; }        /* Internal CSS */
</style>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="external.css"> <!-- p { color: green; } -->

<p style="color: red;" class="text">What color am I?</p>
<!-- Result: RED (inline wins over internal and external) -->
```

**Best Practices:**
- Use **external CSS** for production websites
- Use **internal CSS** for single-page prototypes
- Use **inline CSS** sparingly for dynamic styles or quick fixes
- Link CSS files in `<head>` for better performance

**CSS Selector Types:**

| Selector Type | Syntax | Description | Specificity |
|---------------|--------|-------------|-------------|
| **Universal** | `*` | Selects all elements | 0 |
| **Element/Type** | `div`, `p`, `h1` | Selects by tag name | 1 |
| **Class** | `.class-name` | Selects by class attribute | 10 |
| **ID** | `#id-name` | Selects by id attribute | 100 |
| **Attribute** | `[attr="value"]` | Selects by attribute | 10 |
| **Descendant** | `div p` | Selects nested elements | Combined |
| **Child** | `div > p` | Selects direct children | Combined |
| **Adjacent Sibling** | `h2 + p` | Selects immediate next sibling | Combined |
| **General Sibling** | `h2 ~ p` | Selects all following siblings | Combined |
| **Pseudo-class** | `:hover`, `:first-child` | Selects element states | 10 |
| **Pseudo-element** | `::before`, `::after` | Selects element parts | 1 |

**Examples:**

```css
/* 1. Universal Selector */
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* 2. Element/Type Selectors */
h1 { font-size: 2em; }
p { line-height: 1.6; }
div { display: block; }

/* 3. Class Selectors */
.container { max-width: 1200px; }
.btn-primary { background-color: blue; }
.text-center { text-align: center; }

/* 4. ID Selectors */
#header { position: fixed; top: 0; }
#main-content { margin: 20px; }
#footer { background-color: #333; }

/* 5. Attribute Selectors */
input[type="text"] { border: 1px solid #ccc; }
input[type="email"] { background-color: #f9f9f9; }
a[href^="https"] { color: green; }        /* Starts with */
a[href$=".pdf"] { color: red; }           /* Ends with */
a[href*="example"] { font-weight: bold; }  /* Contains */

/* 6. Descendant Selectors (space) */
.sidebar p { font-size: 14px; }     /* Any p inside .sidebar */
.nav ul li { display: inline; }      /* Any li inside ul inside .nav */

/* 7. Child Selectors (>) */
.menu > li { float: left; }          /* Direct li children of .menu */
article > p { margin-bottom: 15px; } /* Direct p children of article */

/* 8. Adjacent Sibling (+) */
h2 + p { margin-top: 0; }            /* First p immediately after h2 */
.alert + .content { margin-top: 20px; }

/* 9. General Sibling (~) */
h2 ~ p { color: #666; }              /* All p elements after h2 */
.header ~ .section { padding-top: 60px; }

/* 10. Pseudo-classes */
a:hover { color: red; }
a:visited { color: purple; }
li:first-child { font-weight: bold; }
li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
tr:nth-child(even) { background-color: #f2f2f2; }
input:focus { border-color: blue; }

/* 11. Pseudo-elements */
p::first-line { font-weight: bold; }
p::first-letter { font-size: 2em; }
.quote::before { content: "\201C"; }  /* Opening quote */
.quote::after { content: "\201D"; }   /* Closing quote */

/* 12. Combining Selectors */
.container .card.featured { border: 2px solid gold; }
#sidebar .widget:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
input[type="text"]:focus { outline: 2px solid blue; }
```

