**When to Use Viewport Units:**

**â Good Use Cases:**
- Full-screen sections
- Hero banners
- Modal overlays
- Responsive typography
- Mobile-first designs
- Creative layouts

**â Avoid For:**
- Small UI elements (buttons, icons)
- Text that needs to remain readable
- Elements that need consistent sizing
- When accessibility is crucial (very small text on large screens)

**Best Practices:**

```css
/* Combine with other units for safety */
font-size: clamp(1rem, 4vw, 3rem);

/* Set minimums and maximums */
width: min(90vw, 1200px);
height: max(50vh, 300px);

/* Use calc() for complex calculations */
padding: calc(2vh + 10px);
```

**Reset CSS** vs **Normalize CSS** are two approaches to handle browser default styling inconsistencies.

**Comparison:**

| Aspect | Reset CSS | Normalize CSS |
|--------|-----------|---------------|
| **Approach** | Remove all default styles | Preserve useful defaults, fix inconsistencies |
| **File Size** | Smaller | Larger |
| **Styling** | Start from zero | Start from consistent base |
| **Accessibility** | May remove helpful defaults | Preserves accessibility features |
| **Maintenance** | More custom styling needed | Less custom styling needed |

**Reset CSS Examples:**

```css
/* Simple Reset CSS */
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* More Comprehensive Reset */
*, *::before, *::after {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

html {
  line-height: 1.15;
  -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;
}

body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
}

h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  font-size: inherit;
  font-weight: inherit;
  margin: 0;
}

a {
  color: inherit;
  text-decoration: inherit;
}

button, input, select, textarea {
  font: inherit;
  color: inherit;
  background: none;
  border: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0;
}

ul, ol {
  list-style: none;
}

img {
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
}

table {
  border-collapse: collapse;
  border-spacing: 0;
}

/* Eric Meyer's Reset CSS (Popular) */
html, body, div, span, applet, object, iframe,
h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6, p, blockquote, pre,
a, abbr, acronym, address, big, cite, code,
del, dfn, em, img, ins, kbd, q, s, samp,
small, strike, strong, sub, sup, tt, var,
b, u, i, center,
dl, dt, dd, ol, ul, li,
fieldset, form, label, legend,
table, caption, tbody, tfoot, thead, tr, th, td,
article, aside, canvas, details, embed, 
figure, figcaption, footer, header, hgroup, 
menu, nav, output, ruby, section, summary,
time, mark, audio, video {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  border: 0;
  font-size: 100%;
  font: inherit;
  vertical-align: baseline;
}
```

**Normalize CSS Examples:**

```css
/* Normalize.css v8.0.1 (excerpt) */

/* Document */
html {
  line-height: 1.15; /* Correct line height in all browsers */
  -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; /* Prevent font scaling in landscape */
}

/* Sections */
body {
  margin: 0; /* Remove default margin */
}

main {
  display: block; /* Render consistently in IE */
}

h1 {
  font-size: 2em;
  margin: 0.67em 0; /* Correct margin in Chrome, Firefox, Safari */
}

/* Grouping content */
hr {
  box-sizing: content-box; /* Show overflow in Edge and IE */
  height: 0;
  overflow: visible;
}

pre {
  font-family: monospace, monospace; /* Correct inheritance in all browsers */
  font-size: 1em;
}

/* Text-level semantics */
a {
  background-color: transparent; /* Remove gray background in IE10 */
}

abbr[title] {
  border-bottom: none;
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-decoration: underline dotted;
}

b, strong {
  font-weight: bolder; /* Correct weight in Chrome, Edge, Safari */
}

code, kbd, samp {
  font-family: monospace, monospace;
  font-size: 1em;
}

small {
  font-size: 80%;
}

/* Forms */
button, input, optgroup, select, textarea {
  font-family: inherit;
  font-size: 100%;
  line-height: 1.15;
  margin: 0;
}

button, input {
  overflow: visible;
}

button, select {
  text-transform: none;
}

button, [type="button"], [type="reset"], [type="submit"] {
  -webkit-appearance: button;
}
```

**Custom Modern Reset (Popular approach):**

```css
/* Modern CSS Reset */

/* Box sizing rules */
*, *::before, *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Remove default margin */
* {
  margin: 0;
}

/* Remove list styles on ul, ol elements with a list role */
ul[role='list'], ol[role='list'] {
  list-style: none;
}

/* Set core root defaults */
html:focus-within {
  scroll-behavior: smooth;
}

/* Set core body defaults */
body {
  min-height: 100vh;
  text-rendering: optimizeSpeed;
  line-height: 1.5;
  font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
}

/* A elements that don't have a class get default styles */
a:not([class]) {
  text-decoration-skip-ink: auto;
}

/* Make images easier to work with */
img, picture {
  max-width: 100%;
  display: block;
}

/* Inherit fonts for inputs and buttons */
input, button, textarea, select {
  font: inherit;
}

/* Remove all animations and transitions for people who prefer not to see them */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  html:focus-within {
   scroll-behavior: auto;
  }
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    scroll-behavior: auto !important;
  }
}
```

**When to Use Each:**

**Use Reset CSS When:**
- Building a completely custom design system
- Want full control over all styling
- Working on a unique design that doesn't follow web conventions
- Team prefers to style everything from scratch

**Use Normalize CSS When:**
- Want to maintain browser defaults that make sense
- Building on top of existing design systems
- Prioritizing accessibility
- Want consistent styling with minimal effort
- Working with content-heavy sites (blogs, documentation)

**Practical Implementation:**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <!-- Option 1: CDN Normalize -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/normalize/8.0.1/normalize.min.css">

  <!-- Option 2: Custom Reset -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="reset.css">

  <!-- Your main styles -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="main.css">
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Heading with consistent styling</h1>
  <p>Paragraph with predictable appearance</p>
  <button>Button that looks the same everywhere</button>
</body>
</html>
```

**Modern Approach:**
Many developers now use a **hybrid approach** - a lightweight reset combined with normalize-like fixes for specific elements:

```css
/* Hybrid approach */
@import url('normalize.css'); /* For complex form elements */

/* Custom reset for layout elements */
*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }
body, h1, h2, h3, h4, p, ul, ol, li { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }
```

