**CSS Flexbox** is a 1D layout method for arranging items in rows or columns with flexible sizing.

**Key Concepts:**
- **Flex Container**: Parent with `display: flex`
- **Flex Items**: Direct children of flex container
- **Main Axis**: Primary axis (horizontal by default)
- **Cross Axis**: Perpendicular to main axis (vertical by default)

```css
/* Basic Flexbox Setup */
.flex-container {
  display: flex;
  /* flex-direction: row (default) | row-reverse | column | column-reverse */
  flex-direction: row;
  /* justify-content: aligns items along main axis */
  justify-content: space-between;
  /* align-items: aligns items along cross axis */
  align-items: center;
  /* flex-wrap: allows items to wrap */
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 20px;
  padding: 20px;
}

.flex-item {
  /* flex-grow: how much to grow */
  flex-grow: 1;
  /* flex-shrink: how much to shrink */
  flex-shrink: 1;
  /* flex-basis: initial size before free space distribution */
  flex-basis: 200px;
  /* Shorthand: flex: grow shrink basis */
  flex: 1 1 200px;
}
```

**Common Alignment Patterns:**
```css
/* Center everything */
.center-all {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}

/* Navigation bar */
.navbar {
