**CSS Container Queries** allow you to apply styles based on the size of a containing element rather than the viewport, enabling true component-based responsive design.

**Basic Container Query Syntax:**
```css
/* Define a containment context */
.card-container {
  container-type: inline-size; /* or: size, normal */
  container-name: card; /* optional name */
}

/* Shorthand */
.card-container {
  container: card / inline-size;
}

/* Query the container */
@container card (min-width: 300px) {
  .card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
  }

  .card__image {
    width: 40%;
  }

  .card__content {
    width: 60%;
    padding: 1rem;
  }
}

@container card (min-width: 500px) {
  .card__title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  .card__description {
    display: block; /* Show full description */
  }
}
```

**Practical Example - Responsive Card Component:**
```css
.card-wrapper {
  container: card-context / inline-size;
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 600px;
}

.card {
  background: white;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  overflow: hidden;
}

/* Small container - stacked layout */
@container card-context (max-width: 299px) {
  .card {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .card__image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .card__content {
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .card__description {
    display: -webkit-box;
    -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
    -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
}

/* Medium container - horizontal layout */
@container card-context (min-width: 300px) and (max-width: 499px) {
  .card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .card__image {
    width: 120px;
    height: 120px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .card__content {
    padding: 1rem;
    flex: 1;
  }
}

/* Large container - expanded layout */
@container card-context (min-width: 500px) {
  .card {
    display: flex;
  }

  .card__image {
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .card__content {
    padding: 2rem;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .card__title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .card__description {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
}
```

**Container Query vs Media Query:**
```css
/* Media Query - responds to viewport */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .sidebar {
    width: 300px;
  }
}

/* Container Query - responds to parent container */
.layout {
  container: layout / inline-size;
}

@container layout (min-width: 768px) {
  .sidebar {
    width: 300px;
  }
}
```

**Advanced Container Query Features:**
```css
/* Multiple container queries */
.widget-container {
  container: widget / inline-size;
}

@container widget (min-width: 200px) {
  .widget { padding: 1rem; }
}

@container widget (min-width: 400px) {
  .widget {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
}

@container widget (min-width: 600px) {
  .widget {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }
}

/* Container query with height */
.tall-container {
  container: tall / size; /* Both width and height */
  height: 500px;
}

@container tall (min-height: 400px) {
  .content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }
}

/* Logical operators */
@container (min-width: 300px) and (max-width: 600px) {
  .element {
    background: lightblue;
  }
}

@container (min-width: 400px) or (min-height: 300px) {
  .element {
    border: 2px solid blue;
  }
}
```

**JavaScript Integration:**
```javascript
// Check container query support
if ('container' in document.documentElement.style) {
  console.log('Container queries supported!');
} else {
  console.log('Container queries not supported');
  // Load polyfill or provide fallback
}

// Dynamic container sizing
function resizeContainer(element, width) {
  element.style.width = width + 'px';
  // Container queries will automatically respond
}

// Observe container size changes
const resizeObserver = new ResizeObserver(entries => {
  for (let entry of entries) {
    const { width, height } = entry.contentRect;
    console.log(`Container resized to: ${width}x${height}`);
  }
});

resizeObserver.observe(document.querySelector('.card-container'));
```

**When to Use Container Queries:**

**Use Container Queries when:**
- Building reusable components
- Component layout depends on available space
- Creating design systems
- Components are used in different contexts
- Need intrinsic responsive design

**Use Media Queries when:**
- Global layout changes
- Typography scaling across devices
- Navigation patterns
- Viewport-specific features
- Overall page structure

**Browser Support & Fallbacks:**
```css
/* Progressive enhancement approach */
.card {
  /* Base styles for all browsers */
  padding: 1rem;
}

/* Media query fallback */
@media (min-width: 500px) {
  .card {
    display: flex;
  }
}

/* Container query enhancement */
@supports (container-type: inline-size) {
  .card-container {
    container: card / inline-size;
  }

  @container card (min-width: 300px) {
    .card {
      display: flex;
    }
  }
}
```

Container Queries represent the future of responsive design, enabling true component-based styling that responds to context rather than just viewport size.

Modern CSS provides powerful layout systems: **CSS Grid** for 2D layouts, **Flexbox** for 1D layouts, and **CSS Subgrid** for nested grids.

**CSS Grid - 2D Layout System:**
```css
/* Basic Grid Layout */
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
  grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
  gap: 1rem;
  min-height: 100vh;
}

/* Named Grid Areas */
.layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas:
    "header header header"
    "sidebar main aside"
    "footer footer footer";
  grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 150px;
  grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
}

.header { grid-area: header; }
.sidebar { grid-area: sidebar; }
.main { grid-area: main; }
.aside { grid-area: aside; }
.footer { grid-area: footer; }

/* Advanced Grid Features */
.advanced-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr);
  gap: 1rem;
}

.item-1 {
  grid-column: 1 / 5;  /* Span 4 columns */
  grid-row: 1 / 3;     /* Span 2 rows */
}

.item-2 {
  grid-column: 5 / -1; /* From column 5 to end */
  grid-row: 1;
}
```

